    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nWhen I do call `nvim_open_win` with options `split` (suppose `='right'`) and `row` or/and `col` set (suppose `row=5`), neovim just silently exits, without any error message (also terminal IS NOT broken, so it exits gracefully at least). Exit status code is 139.\r\nRunning in lldb debugger:\r\n```\r\nProcess 52379 stopped and restarted: thread 1 received signal: SIGCHLD\r\nProcess 52379 exited with status = 139 (0x0000008b)\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\nminimal.lua:\r\n```lua\r\nvim.api.nvim_open_win(0, false, {\r\n    split = \"right\",\r\n    -- row = 10,\r\n    col = 10,\r\n})\r\n```\r\nThen run: `nvim --clean -u minimal.lua`\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nAt least print error message, do not exit silently.\r\nDocument this case? (I'm not sure if I'm using this function right)\r\n\r\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\r\n\r\nNVIM v0.10.1 commit b0a042e\r\n\r\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\r\n\r\nidk\r\n\r\n### Operating system/version\r\n\r\nArchLinux\r\n\r\n### Terminal name/version\r\n\r\nst 0.9.2\r\n\r\n### $TERM environment variable\r\n\r\ntmux-256color\r\n\r\n### Installation\r\n\r\nsystem package manager (pacman)",
